<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1488" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1488">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/221</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                            <gloss type="from">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                            <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1423. The following telegram received from The Hague:</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>Captain steamship <hi rend="italic">Elfland</hi>, engaged Belgium
                                relief and flying our commission’s flag, reports his vessel attacked
                                Sunday by German aeroplane off Dutch coast. Five bombs were dropped.
                                One struck within 20 feet of ship. I have asked German Minister here
                                to obtain explanation from Berlin.</p>
                        </quote>
                        <p>Please bring to the attention of the German Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>